utting - 'cos he were one for dodging work. So - Ned Flue come one time he kept the - he kept a shop, it was - down where Garners used to be, down Brass cutting, the barbers. Well - he said, here, he said, I've got a suit what'll fit you. Old Dodger said,
 
all right, he said, I'-l go in and get it. So went in, old Ned Flue pulled this here - pulled this suit out you know, and - here, take it home and try it. So - it was about Monday you know old Flue said, here, he said, you haven't been and paid none off t
h
is suit. No, said Dodger, you give him to I. I never give him to you, you've got to - look here, he said, this is in the barber's shop. His brother couldn't shave for laughing. So - he said, I'll tell you what it is Rod, he said, you know. I said, what' -
 what's that?
