Well Jack Pearce's business he had a - that was up Straits, you know that - that big' round house don't you, that was a butcher's shop first and - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Lawrence{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} had it. That w
as when the - when they said - eighteen pence, one and eightpence lady. She used to go and buy her meat, oh - well what's wrong here, eighteen pence, one and eightpence? They couldn't get out of it. There you are see, eighteen pence, he was right enough, 
eighteen pence, one and eightpence. But he wouldn't say one and six see. No fear, he said eighteenpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2562708 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7431414\charrsid29954 What happened to the cobbler's business?
